    {
      "term": "Plucking table",
      "definition": "The flat-topped, pruned shape maintained in cultivated tea gardens that keeps all growing tips at a uniform, harvestable height."
    },
    {
      "term": "Two leaves and a bud",
      "definition": "The standard plucking method for high-quality teas: only the terminal bud and the two youngest leaves below it are harvested. This portion has the highest concentration of flavour compounds, polyphenols, and L-theanine."
    },
    {
      "term": "Flush",
      "definition": "A distinct harvest period within a tea-growing season. Particularly used in Indian tea: first flush (spring), second flush (summer), monsoon flush, and autumnal flush each have characteristic flavour profiles."
