    {
      "term": "Astringency",
      "definition": "A drying, gripping, puckering tactile sensation in the mouth caused by tannins binding to salivary proteins. Distinct from bitterness. Desirable at moderate levels; unpleasant when excessive due to over-extraction."
    },
    {
      "term": "Gongfu style (Gongfu Cha)",
      "definition": "A Chinese brewing approach using a small vessel (gaiwan or small teapot), high leaf-to-water ratio, and multiple very short infusions. Allows careful tracking of the tea's evolution across steepings. Also the name for the formalised Chinese tea ceremony built around this method."
