          "type": "text",
          "content": "In Section 1 you learned that all true tea comes from a single species: Camellia sinensis. Now we need to get more precise, because 'Camellia sinensis' covers quite a lot of ground.\n\nImagine you're a wine producer. You know that 'grape' is the right fruit for wine, but you also know that a Pinot Noir grape and a Shiraz grape are deeply different things, even though they're both grapes, both Vitis vinifera, both fermented into wine. The variety determines the character. The same logic applies to tea.\n\nCamellia sinensis has two primary botanical varieties that matter enormously to what ends up in your cup."
